-- Factbox: Southwest to buy AirTran for $1.04 billion
-- 
-- Mon Sep 27, 2010 11:23am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/09/27/us-airtran-southwest-factbox-idUSTRE68Q2RA20100927

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Southwest Airlines said it would acquire AirTran Holdings Inc for about $1.04 billion in cash and stock to beef up its regional and low-fare services. 

 Below are facts about the two carriers: SOUTHWEST AIRLINES * Flies 3,200 flights a day to 69 U.S. cities. Headquartered at Love Field airport in Dallas. * Incorporated in 1971 with just three aircraft serving three Texas cities. It currently operates 544 Boeing 737 jets, which fly an average of six flights a day. * Has been profitable for 37 consecutive years. * Southwest 2009 net income: $99 million. Average passenger load factor: 76 percent. * Flies out of Las Vegas 224 times a day, Chicago Midway 216 times daily. * Consumed 1.4 billion gallons of jet fuel in 2009. Served 14 million alcoholic beverages. AIRTRAN * Headquartered in Orlando, Florida, with a hub in Atlanta. * Fleet includes 86 Boeing 717s, 52 Boeing 737s * First commercial carrier to offer XM Satellite Radio in every seat on every flight * Ranked the No. 1 low-cost carrier in the Airline Quality Rating study for the past three years. * Serves 71 cities, mostly on the U.S. East Coast, the Midwest and the Caribbean. * 2009 sales $2.9 billion. Profitable nine out of last 10 years. Source: Southwest.com, AirTran.com, annual reports. (Editing by Maureen Bavdek)